17 SECTION 2.
18 Chapter 2 of Title 21 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to elections and
19 primaries generally, is amended by revising Code Section 21-2-2, relating to definitions, by
20 adding new paragraphs to read as follows:
21 "(11.1) 'Multistate voter list maintenance organization' means any entity, organization,
22 consortium, or cooperative agreement among states or jurisdictions that involves the
23 sharing of voter registration data for the purpose of voter list maintenance."
24 "(39.1) 'Voter list maintenance' means the process of ensuring the accuracy and currency
25 of voter registration lists, including, but not limited to, removing ineligible voters and
26 updating records."
27 SECTION 3.
28 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 21-2-225, relating to restrictions
29 on public inspection of applications for voter registration and data on electors, and
30 membership of Secretary of State in nongovernmental entity for purpose of improving voter
31 registration systems, as follows:
32 "21-2-225.
33 (a) Neither the original applications for voter registration nor any copies thereof shall be
34 open for public inspection except upon order of a court of competent jurisdiction.
35 (b) Except as provided in Code Section 21-2-225.1, all data collected and maintained on
36 electors whose names appear on the list of electors maintained by the Secretary of State
37 pursuant to this article shall be available for public inspection with the exception of bank
38 statements submitted pursuant to subsection (c) of Code Section 21-2-220 and
39 subsection (c) of Code Section 21-2-417, the month and day of birth, the social security
40 numbers, email addresses, and driver's license numbers of the electors, and the locations
41 at which the electors applied to register to vote, which shall remain confidential and shall
42 be used only for voter registration purposes; provided, however, that any and all
