50 (c) It shall be the duty of the Secretary of State to furnish copies of such data as may be
51 collected and maintained on electors whose names appear on the list of electors maintained
52 by the Secretary of State pursuant to this article, within the limitations provided in this
53 article, on electronic media or computer run list or both. Notwithstanding any other
54 provision of law to the contrary, the Secretary of State shall establish the cost to be charged
55 for such data. The Secretary of State may contract with private vendors to make such data
56 available in accordance with this subsection. Such data may not be used by any person for
57 commercial purposes.
58 (d)(1) The Secretary of State may become a member of a nongovernmental entity whose
59 purpose is to share and exchange information in order to improve the accuracy and
60 efficiency of voter registration systems. The membership of the nongovernmental entity
61 shall be composed solely of election officials of state and territorial governments of the
62 United States, except that such membership may also include election officials of the
63 District of Columbia.
64 (2) Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, the Secretary of State may
65 share confidential and exempt information after becoming a member of such
66 nongovernmental entity as provided in paragraph (1) of this subsection.
67 (3) The Secretary of State may become a member of such nongovernmental entity only
68 if such entity is controlled and operated by the participating jurisdictions. The entity shall
69 not be operated or controlled by the federal government or any other entity acting on
