77 (5) Notwithstanding any law to the contrary, upon the Secretary of State becoming a
78 member of a nongovernmental entity as provided in this subsection, any information
79 received by the Secretary of State prior to the effective date of this subsection from the
80 a nongovernmental entity whose purpose was to share and exchange information in order
81 to improve the accuracy and efficiency of voter registration systems is exempt from
82 disclosure under Article 4 of Chapter 18 of Title 50, relating to open records, and any
83 other provision of law. However, the Secretary of State may provide such information
84 to the boards of registrars to conduct voter registration list maintenance activities.
85 (e)(1) The Secretary of State or any other state department, agency, board, bureau, office,
86 commission, public corporation, or authority or any board of registrars or election
87 superintendent shall be prohibited from joining or participating in any multistate voter list
88 maintenance organization that:
89 (A) Requires or encourages the contacting of individuals who are not currently
90 registered to vote with the intent to register them to vote; or
91 (B) Shares voter data outside of the explicit purpose of removing deceased, duplicate,
92 or otherwise ineligible voters from the list of electors.
93 (2) The Secretary of State or any other state department, agency, board, bureau, office,
94 commission, public corporation, or authority or any board of registrars or election
95 superintendent shall terminate participation in any multistate voter list maintenance
