122 (2) When an elector of this state moves to another state and the registration officials in
123 such other state or a nongovernmental entity as described in subsection (d) of Code
124 Section 21-2-225 send a notice of cancellation or other information indicating that the
125 elector has moved to such state but such notice or information does not include a copy
126 of such elector's voter registration application in such other state bearing the elector's
127 signature, the Secretary of State or the board of registrars, as the case may be, shall send
128 a confirmation notice to the elector as provided in Code Section 21-2-234.
129 (3) Once becoming a member of the nongovernmental entity described in subsection (d)
130 of Code Section 21-2-225, the Secretary of State shall obtain regular information from
131 such entity regarding electors who may have moved to another state, died, or otherwise
132 become ineligible to vote in Georgia. The Secretary of State shall use such information
133 to conduct list maintenance on the list of eligible electors."
134 SECTION 5.
135 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
136 without such approval.
137 SECTION 6.
138 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
